            Kenneth McIntyre
            </a>
        </p>

        <p>
            The aim of this project is to provide an overview of the many
            critics of Enlightenment rationalism. The essays on each thinker
            are intended not merely to offer an overview of that thinker, but
            also to place him or her in the context of this larger stream of
            anti-rationalist thought. Below is a list of chapters,
            along with the author for the chapter, and a link to the
            abstract, if available.
        </p>

